function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> occursin('A':'Z', first(w)), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` built-in function to iterate over the list of words (`words`) and keep only those where the first letter is a capital letter from A to Z. The `occursin` function is used to check if the range of uppercase letters (`'A':'Z'`) is present in the first character of each word.
